What this package comes with:
1. A site where you can run multiple bots with select plugins.
2. A discord bot:
  Format of / commands : /loot alliance_name ; Gives the alliance loot rankings
  Gives you these slash commands:
    /loot
    /battle-for-berimond
    /nomads
    /warofrealms
    /samurai
    /bloodcrows
    /storm
    /storm-top-players
3. Plugins:
  Alerts:
    Channel 
    Channel Aqua
  Outgoings:
    Channel 
  Chat:
    Channel 
    Hide discord name
  Aqua Island listings / Alerts:
    Channel 
    AlertChannel 
  Aqua Tower listings / Alerts:
    Channel 
    AlertChannel 
  Fortress listings:
    Channel 

  Shutdown Timer:
    Hours
  Attack Fortresses (Kingdom)
  Attack Barrons (Fire)
  Attack Aqua Forts:
    Easy forts only
    Add worser forts
    Hard forts prioritized
    Buy coins
    Buy decos
    Buy XP
  Attack Khan:
    Commander white list
    Lowest banners/chests first
    Waves till chests
  Attack Nomads:
    No chests
    Uses only tools
    Lowest chests first
  Attack Samurai:
    No chests
    Uses only tools
    Lowest chests first
  Attack Beri (Invasion):
    Uses only tools
    Lowest chests first
  Replace Mead Storm

Some info on the plugins:
  Fortress plugins will only send 2 waves on both flanks though having a mead com can reduce that to one flank
  Beri cooldown is bypassed.
  The incoming messages will come with a preview of the attack.
  Replace Mead Storm will only replace mead if it sees there is 2.1 hours left.
  Khan does NOT replace your defence at the current becareful when running for too long.

What you need to do to use (Windows):
  Goto release download the powershell file run it and it should be on your desktop
  Then go in there and press start.bat
What you need to do to use (Other OS):
1. grab the latest version of NodeJS
4. goto the directory of the bot in and run in the terminal
5. chmod 775 start.sh
6. ./start.sh
7. then you can configure ./ggeConfig.json or let it generate one for you.

For Discord:
1. https://discord.com/developers/applications to create a bot
2. Within your application in Settings goto Bot from there you will find Presence Intent enable all of them from here you will
also find Token goto the ggeConfig and place it under discordToken.

3. Proceed to General Information and scroll down till you see Application ID place it under discordClientId.
4. Next head to Oauth2 and take the Client Secret and within ggeconfig place it under discordClientSecret.
5. In the same section you'll see redirects take the discordPort and add these links:
  http://127.0.0.1:(discordPort here)
  https://127.0.0.1:(discordPort here)
Optionally if you are hosting for others:
  http/s://webaddress:(discordPort here)
6. From here restart the bot and press the "Link Discord" 
